* Editor’s note: This livestream has ended. SOWETO - As tributes continue to pour in for struggle icon Winnie Madikizela-Mandela, a church service is being held at the Methodist Church in Meadowlands to honour her. This is where Mama Winnie attended a five-hour service just days before her passing. ANC leaders are expected to attend church services across the country. Those who want to write messages of support for Mam' Winnie's family can do so in condolence books at various centres around the country and abroad. Government will host a memorial service at Orlando Stadium on 11 April. Madikizela-Mandela's official funeral will take place on 14 April. eNCA